<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536424>
    dc:description "Fig. 7. Charinus Simon, 1892, female gonopods, dorsal view (left column) and detail (right column). A–B. Charinus acaraje Pinto-da-Rocha, Machado & Weygoldt, 2002 (MNRJ 9297). C–D. Charinus palikur sp. nov. (AMCC [LP 3831]) E–F. Charinus sooretama sp. nov. (MNRJ 9245)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5536424/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536428>
    dc:description "Fig. 9. Charinus Simon, 1892, male gonopods. A–B. Charinus euclidesi sp. nov. (MNRJ 9099), ventral view (A), posterior view (B). C–D. Charinus sooretama sp. nov. (MNRJ 9245), ventral view (B), detail of sinistral side showing lamina medialis, lateral lobe 1 and 2, and dorsal lobe (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5536428/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536583>
    dc:description "Fig. 75. Charinus sooretama sp. nov. (MNRJ 9245), general morphology, ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Sternum, ventral view. C. Frontal process. D. Pedipalp tarsus, frontal view. E. Pedipalp, dorsal view. F. Pedipalp, ventral view. Scale bars: A = 1 cm; B = 1 mm; C = 0.1 mm; D = 0.5 mm; E–F = 0.5 cm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5536583/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536422>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Charinus Simon, 1892, female gonopods, dorsal (left column) and posterior (right column) views. A–B. Charinus renneri sp. nov. (MNRJ 9198). C–D. Charinus euclidesi sp. nov. (MNRJ 9099). E–F. Charinus carioca sp. nov. (MNRJ 9201). Scale bars: A–D = 0.25 mm; E–F = 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5536422/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536519>
    dc:description "Fig. 48. Charinus brasilianus Weygoldt, 1972, general morphology (MNRJ 9271). A. Female habitus, dorsal view. B. Male habitus, dorsal view. C. Female pedipalp, dorsal view. D. Female pedipalp, ventral view. E. Male pedipalp, dorsal view. F. Male pedipalp, ventral view. G. Frontal process. H. Sternum, ventral view. Scale bars: A, C–F = 1 mm; B = 5 mm; G = 0.1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5536519/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536426>
    dc:description "Fig. 8. Charinus Simon, 1892, male gonopods. A–B. Charinus acaraje Pinto-da-Rocha, Machado & Weygoldt, 2002 (MNRJ 9297), ventral view (A) and detail of dorsal lobe (LoD) and lateral lobe 1 (LoL1). C–D. Charinus brasilianus Weygoldt, 1972 (MNRJ 9226), posterior view (C) and detail of lateral lobes 1 and 2 (LoL1, 2), dorsal lobe (LoD) and lamina medialis (LaM) (D). E–H. Charinus carajas Giupponi & Miranda, 2016 (MZSP 29126), ventral view of gonopod (E), detail of sinistral side of gonopod (F), detail of LoL1 and LoD (G), and detail of LoL2 (H)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5536426/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536517>
    dc:description "Fig. 47. Charinus apiaca sp. nov. (MNRJ 9286), general morphology, ♀. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Sternum, ventral view. C. Frontal process. D. Pedipalp tarsus, frontal view. E. Pedipalp, dorsal view. F. Pedipalp, ventral view. Scale bars: A, D–F = 1 mm; B–C = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5536517/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536420>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. Charinus Simon, 1892, female gonopods, dorsal (left column) and posterior (right column) views. A–B. Charinus apiaca sp. nov. (MNRJ 9286). C–D. Charinus gertschi Goodnight & Goodnight, 1946 (AMCC [LP 10076]). E–F. Charinus miskito sp. nov. (SMNS). G–H. Charinus mocoa sp. nov. (SMF 68). Scale bars: A–B, F–H = 0.1 mm; C–E, I–L = 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5536420/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536521>
    dc:description "Fig. 49. Charinus carinae sp. nov. (MNRJ 9293), general morphology, ♂. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Sternum, ventral view. C. Frontal process. D. Pedipalp tarsus, frontal view. E. Pedipalp, dorsal view. F. Pedipalp, ventral view. Scale bars: A = 5 mm; B, D–F = 1 mm; C = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5536521/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536416>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Charinidae Quintero, 1986, pedipalp femur, prolateral and dorsal views. A–B. Charinus carinae sp. nov. (MNRJ 9293). C–D. Charinus gertschi Goodnight & Goodnight, 1946 (AMCC [LP 10076]). E–F. Sarax bispinosus (Nair, 1934) (AMCC [LP 12298]). G–H. Sarax willeyi Gravely, 1915 (SMF). Scale bars: A–D, G–H = 1 mm; E–F = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5536416/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536418>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Charinidae Quintero, 1986, pedipalp patellar articles, dorsal and prolateral views. A–B. Charinus carinae sp. nov. (MNRJ 9293). C–D. Charinus gertschi Goodnight & Goodnight, 1946 (AMCC [LP 10076]). E–F. Sarax bispinosus (Nair, 1934) (AMCC [LP 12298]). G–H. Sarax willeyi Gravely, 1915 (SMF). Scale bars: A–D, G–H = 1 mm; E–F = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5536418/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5536430>
    dc:description "Fig. 10. Charinus Simon, 1892, chelicerae, prolateral and retrolateral views. A–B. Charinus loko sp. nov. (SMNS). C–D. Charinus miskito sp. nov. (SMNS). E–F. Charinus mocoa sp. nov. (SMF 68). G–H. Charinus alagoanus sp. nov. (MNRJ 9295). I–J. Charinus renneri sp. nov. (MNRJ 9198). K–L. Charinus madagascariensis Fage, 1954 (MNHN). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5536430/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

